So far 961 episodes of One Piece have been aired. With a total of 99 reported filler episodes, One Piece has a very low filler percentage of 10%.</p>        <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>One Piece is the story of Monkey D. <h1>One Piece Filler List</h1>
<span class="rdf-meta element-hidden" content="One Piece" property="dc:title"></span><span class="rdf-meta element-hidden" content="0" datatype="xsd:integer" property="sioc:num_replies"></span> <div class="Date"><span class="Prefix">Updated on </span>January 24, 2021</div>
<div class="Description">
<p>One Piece is an ongoing anime series that started in 1999. So far 961 episodes of One Piece have been aired. With a total of 99 reported filler episodes, One Piece has a very low filler percentage of 10%.</p> <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>One Piece is the story of Monkey D. Luffy who became a rubber man after accidently eating a Devil Fruit. In his quest, Luffy builds his crew and continues on his adventure to find the mysterious treasure One Piece.</p>
</div></div></div> </div>

import json
In [9]:
numbers = soup.select('td.Number')
titles = soup.select('td.Title>a')
types = soup.select('td.Type>span')
dates = soup.select('td.Date')
In [10]:
for i in range(len(numbers)): 
    numbers[i] = numbers[i].getText()
    titles[i] = titles[i].getText()
    types[i] = types[i].getText()
    dates[i] = dates[i].getText()
In [11]:
onePiece = []
for i in range(len(numbers)):
    if types[i] == 'Filler':
        y = 'red'
    else:
        y = 'green'
    x = {'id': numbers[i], 'title': titles[i], 'type': types[i], 'date': dates[i], 'class': y}
    onePiece.append(x)
